implementere løsninger i Oracle Cloud (OCI) og CX (Eloqua, Responsys, mm). Under OCI er der services som Oracle Integration Cloud, OCI Dataflow, OCI Datalake, mm.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4247671810/','2025-06-16',88,NULL,'[\"JavaScript\", \"Linux\", \"Apache\", \"Apache Spark\", \"Data Analytics\", \"Design\", \"Eloqua\", \"Infrastruktur\", \"Marketingsanalyse\", \"Marketingsmekanisering\"]','2025-06-30 11:23:58','2025-06-30 11:23:58'),(5,4246271747,'Software Engineer',5,'Malmø, Skåne len, Sverige','Om jobbet\n\n** This is a 14-month contract position. \n\n\n\n\nPosition Description\n\n\n\n\nCraft tested, high quality code in JavaScript, SQL and Cloud infra\nWork collaboratively with other disciplines, including architecture, product, experience design, data specialists and domain experts\nMake changes in a compliant and efficient way through integration and deployment pipelines\nValue variant testing and implement meaningful experiments as a way of solving the right problems\nValue system design and modelling as an important part of software engineering\n\n\n\n\nRequired Skills and Experience \n\n\n\n\nProficiency with the JavaScript Language\nBuilding Cloud Native systems and solutions at scale\nCommunicating clearly and effectively in written and oral form to share knowledge, experiences, and collaborate well','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4246271747/','2025-06-16',100,NULL,'[\"Cloud Infrastructure\", \"JavaScript\", \"SQL\", \"Cloud-Native Applications\", \"Software Deployment\", \"Systemdesign\"]','2025-06-30 11:23:58','2025-06-30 11:23:58'),(6,4228960164,'Freelance IT-konsulenter',6,'København, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nHos Edora søger vi dygtige freelance IT-konsulenter indenfor udvikling, test, arkitektur mv. til en række spændende projekter hos os og vores kunder.\n\n\n\n\nEdora har vundet en ny spændende rammeaftale, hvor vi løbende skal levere konsulenter til mange forskelligartede opgaver. Derudover samarbejder vi med en række private som offentlige samarbejdspartnere, såsom Skattestyrelsen og Styrelsen for Arbejdsmarkedet og Rekruttering (STAR). Vi har derfor mange spændende projekter på vej, og søger løbende de rette konsulenter til at løse dem.\n\n\n\n\nVi tilbyder:\n\nUdfordrende opgaver hos innovative virksomheder - offentlige og private\nMulighed for at arbejde med de nyeste teknologier\nStærkt fagligt miljø med fokus på vidensdeling og udvikling\n\n\n\n\nBliv en del af et dynamisk og professionelt netværk, hvor din ekspertise gør en forskel! Som medlem vil du desuden modtage invitationer til faglige arrangementer som Tech Tuesday, kurser mv. arrangeret af Edora.\n\n\n\n\nNår du uploader dit CV, vil du blive bedt om at udfylde kontaktoplysninger, hvilke roller du er interesseret i, hvornår du er ledig samt din timepris. Du kan derudover også angive om du alene er interesseret i at arbejde som freelance konsulent, eller du også er interesseret i fastansættelse.\n\n\n\n\nDu kan til ethvert tidspunkt ændre dit CV og oplysninger, så dine oplysninger er opdateret og reflekterer dine nuværende kompetencer. Ligeledes kan du nemt trække dit samtykke tilbage, hvis du ikke længere ønsker at være del af vores netværk.\n\n\n\n\nSend os dit CV via \"Ansøg\" knappen og du hører fra os!','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4228960164/','2025-06-16',100,NULL,'[\".NET\", \"C#\", \"Java\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Teststyring\", \"TypeScript\", \".NET Core\", \"Freelancing\", \"IT-ledelse\", \"Microsoft Azure\"]','2025-06-30 11:23:58','2025-06-30 11:23:58'),(7,4249183456,'Full-Stack Lead Developer',7,'København og omegn','Om jobbet\n\nWe’re looking for an experienced Full-Stack Lead Developer to drive our IT development efforts and help scale our in-house team. In this key role, you’ll work closely with our AI team, collaborate with our external Danish tech partner, and play a pivotal part in shaping the architecture and direction of our solution.\n\n \n\nYou bring strong technical expertise across the stack and thrive in a leadership role - mentoring junior developers, establishing best practices, and creating a culture of high-quality engineering.\n\n \n\nAs a fast-growing fintech scale-up, we empower banks to optimize their core banking business through cutting-edge data analytics and modern technology. Our platform already supports thousands of users across the Nordics, and we’re now expanding globally.\n\n\n\n\nWe are building our development team in Copenhagen to support this growth. If you\'re looking to take ownership in a fast-moving environment, influence real product decisions, and make a tangible impact in the financial sector, we’d love to talk.\n\n\n\n\nWe\'re looking for an outgoing personality who’s not only passionate about clean code and creative solutions, but also brings a collaborative spirit and a sense of humor to the team - someone who loves tech, people, and having fun while working hard.\n\n\n\n\nWhat you get to do:\n\nTake a lead role in a high-growth fintech scale-up\nLead and grow a small, focused development team, setting the technical direction and fostering a strong engineering culture\nDesign and build innovative solutions that drive real transformation in banking\nThrive in a hands-on environment where your work has a direct impact\nCollaborate with a passionate and talented team in a supportive, fast-moving, and purpose-driven culture\n\n\n\n\nTo be successful you have:\n\nStrong technical foundation in our stack (see below) with a passion for clean, scalable code\nOwnership mindset – you take pride in delivering high-quality solutions and seeing things through\nSelf-driven and organized, with a strong sense of responsibility and the ability to meet deadlines\nMentorship experience – you enjoy guiding others and helping junior developers grow\nSolid DevOps skills, including experience with CI/CD pipelines and deployment automation\nReliable technical support instincts, with IT counterparts in banks\nTeam-oriented with a proactive attitude\nStrong communication and collaboration skills\nExperience in banking or fintech is an advantage\nProficiency in a Nordic language is a plus, but not a requirement\n\n\n\n\nTech stack\n\nExtensive hands-on experience with Laravel, PHP, Vue.js, SQL, HTML, and CSS.\nProficiency with RESTful APIs, Docker, Git, and Windows Server.\nFamiliarity with cloud computing and hosting technologies, particularly Azure.\n\n\n\n\nThe position is full time and hybrid - based at our HQ in the center of Copenhagen.\n\n \n\nIf you are ready to bring your skills, energy, and expertise to the forefront of fintech innovation, let’s make it happen together!\n\n \n\nInterviews are performed on an ongoing basis, so please do not hesitate to send across application and CV.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4249183456/','2025-06-23',73,'Hybrid','[\"AngularJS\", \"Backend-webudvikling\", \"CSS\", \"Full-Stack Development\", \"Git\", \"HTML\", \"Laravel\", \"PHP\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Kreativ problemløsning\"]','2025-06-30 11:23:58','2025-06-30 11:23:58'),(8,4248419319,'Software Engineer - Backend (Hyperlocal)',8,'Københavns Kommune, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nAt Too Good To Go, we have an ambitious goal: to inspire and empower everyone to fight food waste together.\n\n40% of all food produced in the world is wasted. And that has a huge impact on the health of our planet, with 10% of greenhouse gas emissions coming from food waste.\n\nWe’re more than an app: we are a certified B Corporation with a mission to empower everyone to take action against food waste, so alongside our marketplace app, we create educational tools, explore new business solutions - such as our Retail Technologies offering, and influence legislation to help reduce food waste.\n\nWe’re growing fast: Our community of 120 million registered users and 247,000 active partners across 19 countries, have together already prevented 453+ million meals from going to waste - avoiding over 1.224.000 tonnes of CO2e!\n\nThe Role\n\nWe are looking for a Backend Software Engineer to join our Hyperlocal team. As a member of a product team, you will work towards specific outcomes with the freedom and responsibility to figure out the best way to achieve them together with the other engineers and team members.\n\nYour mission will be to help refine, design, implement, deliver and maintain various product features, ensuring quality, maintainability, and sustainability. You will be supported by more experienced colleagues who will guide and train you, and encourage you to push your limits and continuously improve.\n\nThe Hyperlocal team works on an internal application to support our Marketplace Health at a Hyperlocal level. The team is responsible for developing and maintaining data pipelines for the fast processing of live data to underpin the application, which encompasses both visualisation tools to help our colleagues in the rest of the company work more efficiently, and features which automate marketplace health interventions.\n\nThe Tech Stack\n\nThe application is built with Spring Boot and Java 21, supporting a web layer built using React and based around Mapbox GL. Data coming from multiple sources and streams are processed with Apache Flink before being stored in a DynamoDB database for use in the application visualisations and automations. Deployment is via AWS, and we are able to run a full development environment locally.\n\nResponsibilities\n\n\nBuild and evolve our solution for managing & optimising Marketplace Health\nWork with our Data and Product Analytics organisations to develop our data processing pipeline with a focus on delivering meaningful health metrics that our business can act on\nActively participate in the team’s agile development processes with a continuous improvement mindset\nStrive to deliver international top-class products with maximum quality, maintainability and scalability\n\n\nThe ideal candidate\n\nFor this team in particular, it is very much advantageous to have experience with big data / streaming data, and, hopefully, Apache Flink.\n\n\nHas worked predominantly in backend development with the Java ecosystem\nHas experience with SpringBoot, NoSQL Databases, RESTful APIs & GIT\nHas experience working with Stream Processing, Event Sourcing, and large data sets\nIs interested in extending their fullstack skills, contributing to our frontend built with React\nIs comfortable using AWS (e.g. S3, Kinesis, DynamoDB), Redis, Docker and Kubernetes\nHas experience building scalable and maintainable solutions\nEnjoys actively participating in a cross-functional tech team\nTakes pride in writing quality code\n\n\nOur values\n\n\nWe win together: Food waste is a big beast to fight. We can do it if we win together as Waste Warriors with no ego. We believe in a #oneteam.\nWe raise the bar: We always push for more. We work smart, smash barriers and elevate one another.\nWe keep it simple: Our ambitions are bold but our solutions are simple.\nWe build a legacy: We’re proud of the change we’re driving. \nWe care: We always look out for each other. Caring is also about the way we do business. We do the right thing.\n\n\nWhat We Have To Offer\n\n\nAn opportunity to work in a global social-impact company and certified B Corporation! where you can see a real and tangible impact in your role.\nTo be an integral member of our defined product teams. We are eager for you to make an impact and contribute to the product scope and development; Your insights are valuable, and we are here to listen.\nWork-life balance is important to us! Focus on the job to be done, not the hours spent, there is no need for overtime. On-call duty is not part of the job, but can be additionally agreed upon should you and your manager both wish it. We believe that happy environments create happy employees. \nWe trust in our employees and encourage an autonomous environment that provides several opportunities for employees to contribute, develop and take ownership of their work in a way that works for them.\nTo be part of an international company, with over 1,300+ colleagues across 19 countries that are on the same important mission.\nAn informal environment, working alongside a tech team of over 190 passionate people, we celebrate our differences and our successes and have a strong values-driven team culture.\nWe work onsite in the office 3 days per week.\nWe may be able to support you with a working visa in Copenhagen, please be prepared to discuss this topic further in your first stage interview.\n\n\nHow To Apply\n\n\nWe take recruitment very seriously, so please carefully read everything we have written above. Please also check our website and international media in order to get a good overview of Too Good To Go.\nSubmit your CV and Cover letter in English.\nPlease note that we only accept applications coming through our platform. No CV or Cover Letter will be accepted by email or LinkedIn direct messaging.\n\n\nJob Ref\n\nA Movement for Everyone\n\nWe want to inspire and empower everyone to fight food waste together. With that mission, it’s only natural that we want to build a diverse and inclusive team of highly capable individuals who are passionate about doing things in a better way. We strongly believe we all excel and are more creative when we’re allowed to be ourselves, and we’re committed to a culture where all of us belong.\n\nWe are an equal opportunity employer and all employment is decided on the basis of qualifications, merit and business need. If you need reasonable accommodation at any point in the application or interview process, please let us know.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4248419319/','2025-06-16',90,NULL,'[\"Backend-webudvikling\", \"Java\", \"JavaScript\", \"OOP\", \"Programmering\", \"REST APIs\", \"React.js\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Webtjenester Amazon (AWS)\", \"REST\"]','2025-06-30 11:24:47','2025-06-30 11:24:47'),(9,4222848827,'Senior Software Engineer (Golang/PHP) | Malmö',9,'Malmø, Skåne len, Sverige','Om jobbet\n\nTHE OPPORTUNITY\n\nDo you believe that the only consistent thing in technology is change? If so, this position is for you!\n\nAt Boozt we are proud to say that we are a tech company at it\'s core and we are now looking for an experienced, self-motivated, and passionate GoLang developer to be part of our in-house team.\n\nOur Order and Return Management systems are developed in-house using a variety of technologies, PHP and Go being the main two. We practice engineering-driven business development and many important decisions are made by our developers. We do regular system maintenance to refactor and upgrade to the latest versions of components and libraries while doing our best to explore and incorporate new technologies and concepts. Our main focus is to be very close to the business units and users but we try to allow technology to guide us in how we make our choices.\n\nOur Medium Page\n\nWhat You Will Do\n\n\nImplement new features and functions needed for the company, when appropriate, have them be influenced by the use of AI and/or machine learning.\nMultiple deployments a day due to continuous integration and an agile workflow.\nAutomate manual tasks to help the business users do their everyday work.\nDevelopment and maintenance in Go.\nYou will interact with product managers and business unit representatives to help determine scopes, plan and specify projects.\nMaintaining and improving system integrations using asynchronous messaging (Google Pub/Sub, RabbitMQ and various APIs).\n\n\n\nYOUR PROFILE\n\n\nBroad experience from working with Go. Experience with PHP and Symfony is a plus.\nExperience with having used appropriate forms of AI for workflow improvements as well as incorporating it into projects or products in meaningful ways.\nExperience in working with other business units in order to understand the needs and improve the system.\nBS or MS degree in Computer Science or a related technical field is desirable.\nFluent in English since this is our corporate language (only applications in English will be considered)\n\n\n\nTechnical Keywords: Go, GoLang, AI, LLM, Machine Learning, PHP, Symfony, Google Cloud Platform, GitLab, Redis, RabbitMQ, PubSub, MySQL, CI/CD, DataDog, ElasticSearch, Manticore, Terraform, a mix of monolith and microservice solutions.\n\nBOOZT PERKS\n\n\nGreat personal and internal career development\nA culture that incorporates our values of trust, freedom, and responsibility\nFlexible work environment\nDriven and passionate international colleagues\nA generous employee discount\nWellness allowance and sports activities, HQ onsite masseuse and medical doctor\n\n\n\nA LITTLE BIT ABOUT US\n\nWe are one of the leading e-commerce players in the Nordics. We offer our customers fashion, kids, sports, beauty, and home on Boozt.com and Booztlet.com. You can find our office in Malmö, Sweden, our Boozt Innovation Lab in the heart of Copenhagen, a data science team in Aarhus, Denmark, our two tech offices in Vilnius, Lithuania, and in Poznan, Poland, and our fully automated warehouse in Ängelholm (one of the worlds biggest AutoStores). Our Boozt family consists of +1000 employees from more than 60+ nationalities; we believe that our diverse teams help us build an innovative and vibrant workplace. \n\nWe are an equal-opportunity employer that embraces diversity and inclusiveness.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4222848827/','2025-06-23',76,NULL,'[\"Backend-webudvikling\", \"Datalogi\", \"JavaScript\", \"Microservices\", \"OOP\", \"SQL\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Integrated Systems\", \"Løbende Integration\", \"XML\"]','2025-06-30 11:24:47','2025-06-30 11:24:47'),(10,4253916065,'Software Engineer',10,'Herlev, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nAbout The Job\n\nYou’ll be joining small, but growing, team of engineers. You’ll be working on developing and improving our current payment and point-of-sale solutions to our customers.\n\n\n\n\nYou’ll have the opportunity to working in a young company that is taking off. There will be lots of possibilities to put theory to practice as we onboard more customers and expand into more countries. You’ll be able to take responsibility and have a direct impact on the solutions we provide.\n\n\n\n\nYou’ll have 5 or more years of experience as a developer with a relevant education in IT or Computer Science.\n\n\n\n\nYou’ll be familiar with multiple of the technologies we use day-to-day.\n\n\n\n\nWhat You\'ll Do\n\n\n\n\nDesign and write maintainable, scalable and testable solutions\nImprove and maintain existing payment, point-of-sale and internal systems\nWork with the team to develop and test new functionality and improvements\nContinuously improve CI/CD pipelines and infrastructure\nCollaborate with product team to define and breakdown new projects into workable tasks\nLead projects with the team\nHelp and mentor the team\nActively participate in improving the systems from a architectural standpoint\n\n\n\n\nWho You Are\n\n\n\n\n5+ years of experience\nExperience with payment systems\nRelevant bachelor or master degrees\n\n\n\n\nTechnologies we work with\n\n\n\n\nBackend\n\nJava, Spring, JUnit\nMySQL, Flyway, RabbitMQ\nPorts & Adapters, Domain Driven Design\nCamunda, MQTT\nGitHub Actions, CircleCI\nDocker, Terraform, AWS ECS\ngit, Github, CI/CD\n\n\n\n\nFrontend\n\nJavaScript, Typescript, React, Html, CSS, TanStack Query\nJest, Playwright\nGitHub Actions, CircleCI\nAWS S3, Cloudflare\ni18n, feature flags,\ngit, Github, CI/CD\n\n\n\n\nAndroid\n\nJava, Kotlin, Android, ReactNative,\nJetpack Compose, MVVM, MQTT, Dagger\nJUnit, Espresso\nGitHub Actions, CircleCI\nGoogle Playstore, Hexnode\ni18n, feature flags, Code Review, git, Github, CI/CD,\nHardware with Scanners, Printers & Payment Terminals\n\n\n\n\nWhy Flatpay?\n\nAs part of our team, you will join over 600 passionate Flatpayers dedicated to shaping the future of payments in Europe. Flatpay is proud to be a company that values diversity. We ensure an inclusive work environment for all our employees and offer opportunities for professional growth and development.\n\n\n\n\nWe have free slushice, an on-site gym, a fully equipped gamer room, and plenty of other fun things at our office!\n\n\n\n\nIf you are ready to be part of this exciting journey, we would love to hear from you today.\n\n\n\n\nAbout Us\n\nWelcome to Flatpay!\n\n\n\n\nFlatpay is not just another payment solution; we are dedicated to innovating the market for payment solutions and financial services in the SME segment with our customer-centric and transparent services.\n\n\n\n\nFlatpay is more than just work. We believe in fostering a vibrant and fun work culture where our ambitious colleagues can thrive. Our goal? To create the next unicorn straight out of Denmark. As part of our team, you will be one of +900 passionate colleagues dedicated to making a difference in the financial world.\n\n\n\n\nWhat sets Flatpay apart is our dedication. We continuously strive to stay ahead of the curve, adapting our solutions to meet our client\'s evolving needs.\n\n\n\n\nLet\'s shape the future of 7 million European merchants together!','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4253916065/','2025-06-25',100,NULL,'[\"Datalogi\", \"Git\", \"Java\", \"JavaScript\", \"OOP\", \"Programmering\", \"React.js\", \"Webtjenester Amazon (AWS)\", \"Android\", \"CI\"]','2025-06-30 11:24:47','2025-06-30 11:24:47'),(11,4254358060,'Senior Software Engineer, PHP',11,'Den Europæiske Union','Om jobbet\n\nAre you a seasoned backend developer who thrives on solving complex problems and shaping scalable architectures? We\'re looking for a Senior Backend Engineer to play a key role in evolving our cutting-edge web streaming platform—enhancing core features, driving our cloud migration to AWS, and mentoring a collaborative, agile team.\n\n\n\n\nThis is more than just maintenance work—it\'s an opportunity to make architectural decisions, influence development culture, and help lead a transition to a modern cloud-first infrastructure.\n\n\n\n\nWhat You Will Do\n\n\n\n\nArchitect, develop, and maintain core backend services using PHP (MVC frameworks) and Node.js\nDesign and implement scalable, secure RESTful APIs\nLead and contribute to our AWS cloud migration, helping us modernize the platform\nCollaborate cross-functionally with developers, product managers, and our Canadian partner team\nAct as a technical mentor, guiding best practices and fostering engineering excellence\nContinuously improve platform performance, scalability, and reliability\nContribute to code reviews, architecture decisions, and process improvement initiatives\n\n\n\n\nWhat You Bring\n\n\n\n\n5+ years of experience in backend development, including PHP and Node.js\nStrong hands-on experience with AWS (e.g., EC2, S3, RDS, Lambda)\nSolid knowledge of SQL databases and performance optimization\nExperience with MVC frameworks (e.g., Laravel, Symfony)\nProven ability to architect complex systems and lead technical projects\nDeep understanding of REST API design and secure integration patterns\nFamiliarity with source control tools (e.g., Git, GitHub/GitLab)\nA collaborative mindset with a knack for building trust-based team relationships\nNatural curiosity and a resourceful, problem-solving attitude\nExcellent spoken and written English—you\'ll work daily with our Canadian counterparts\n\n\n\n\nWhy Join Us\n\n\n\n\nJoin a team that\'s actively shaping the future of a high-traffic streaming platform\nTake ownership and have a real technical impact\nWork in a flexible, remote-friendly environment\nGrow with a company that values technical leadership and continuous learning','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4254358060/','2025-06-26',100,NULL,'[\"Applikationsprogrammeringsgrænseflader\", \"Backend-webudvikling\", \"Datalogi\", \"Node.js\", \"PHP\", \"SQL\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Webtjenester Amazon (AWS)\", \"Store systemer\"]','2025-06-30 11:24:47','2025-06-30 11:24:47'),(12,4248784493,'Softwareudvikler - Integrationer',12,'Albertslund, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nSoftwareudvikler – Integrationer\n\nCoop Danmark, Albertslund\n\nHar du erfaring med at udvikle robuste og skalerbare systemintegrationer? Kan du bringe os til næste niveau indenfor systemintegrationer? Og har du lyst til at arbejde i en af Danmarks største detailhandelsvirksomheder?\n\nSå kom og bliv en del af Coop Teknologi, hvor vi alle bidrager til at udvikle og optimere vores teknologiske platforme. Vi har erstattet 80% af vores systemer, software og infrastruktur med SAP for at skabe en stabil, sikker og fremtidssikker teknologisk platform. Til udvikling og implementering af integrationer, har vi brug for en dygtig Softwareudvikler, der har god erfaring med systemintegrationer.\n\nDit nye team\n\nVi er 12 kolleger i Application Services, der ser frem til, at du starter. Sammen skaber vi et mere lokalt, enkelt og digitalt Coop og en arbejdsplads, hvor vi bryder mønstre, og hvor vi hylder de gode, skæve ideer.\n\nApplication Services, består af 3 teams, et RPA-team, der udvikler software robotter, et Stores team der udvikler butiksnære applikationer og et Integrations team, med ansvar for udvikling og vedligeholdelse af integrationer mellem systemer, standardpakker, cloudservices og eksterne aktører.\n\nAlle teams arbejder tværfunktionelt i Coop og har dermed en stor kontaktflade med de øvrige afdelinger. Vi er et distribueret team og har foruden Danmark også kolleger i Ukraine.\n\nVi arbejder produktorienteret og lægger ansvaret i de respektive teams, da vi tror på, at det er der, de mest kompetente beslutninger kan tages.\n\nOm jobbet\n\nSom ”Softwareudvikler – Integrationer” i Application Services, vil du udvikle og implementere system integrationer på Coops cloud integrationsplatform – i et DevOps organiseret integrationsteam.\n\nDine Hovedopgaver Bliver\n\n\nSammen med det øvrige team at implementere og forbedre værktøjer og processer i afdelingen\nSamarbejde med forretningen, IT-arkitekter, løsningsejere, projektledere, IT-drift og eksterne leverandører\nOpretholde, fastholde og videreudvikle standarder\nForstå og klarlægge komplekse forretningskrav til integrationer og generere elegante og skalerbare løsninger\nUdvikle integrationer til et service orienteret landskab\nArbejde fokuseret i et spændende og udfordrende integrationsteam, hvor vores daglige arbejde organiseres i et agilt mindset, med sprint planning, daily scrum og retrospektiv\n\n\nOm dig\n\nDu er motiveret af integration af systemer og har dit faglige fundament indenfor systemintegrationsområdet og API management, hvor du har flere års erfaring med udvikling af system integrationer mellem større virksomhedssystemer.\n\nI øvrigt forstiller vi os at du har følgende baggrund:\n\n\nerfaring med Spring og Spring Boot\nprogrammeringserfaring med Java\nerfaring med REST / SOAP\nerfaring med teamarbejde\nIT uddannelsesmæssig baggrund som datamatiker, Ingeniør, Cand. IT eller lignende\n\n\nHar du kendskab til Cloud teknologier (Kubernetes / Rancher), Docker, Terraform, Golang og CI/CD (Azure DevOps) er det en fordel.\n\nDet får du hos os i Coop\n\nDu vil opleve en arbejdsplads der viser engagement og interesse, og hvor vi har et fælles mål om at skabe Fremtidens Coop til glæde for vores kunder, vores medarbejdere og vores forretning. Du vil indgå i en afdeling med dygtige kollegaer og teamånd, hvor du får mulighed for at præge din egen karriere.\n\nVi belønner din indsats med en lønpakke, der inkluderer pensionsordning og sundhedsforsikring. Du får også adgang til en række medarbejdergoder, såsom rabat i Coops butikker, sommerhusudlejning, personaleklubber og indkøbsfordele. Du får desuden fleksible arbejdstider og mulighed for hjemmearbejde.\n\nDin arbejdsplads bliver på vores Hovedkontor i Albertslund.\n\nInteresseret?\n\nEr du klar til at blive vores nye ”Softwareudvikler – Integrationer”? Så skynd dig at sende dit CV via vores online ansøgningsformular. Ansøgningsfristen er den 6. juli 2025, men vi holder løbende samtaler, og tager stillingsannoncen ned, når vi har fundet relevante kandidater, så vent ikke for længe.\n\nHar du spørgsmål til jobbet eller ansøgningsprocessen, er du velkommen til at kontakte Anders Dvinge, Manager, Application Services på telefon +45 51 59 45 91 eller mail anders.dvinge@coop.dk\n\nDu kan også læse mere om Coop som arbejdsplads på vores hjemmeside www.coop.dk\n\nVi ser frem til at høre fra dig!','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4248784493/','2025-06-16',65,NULL,'[\"CSS\", \"HTML\", \"Java\", \"JavaScript\", \"OOP\", \"Programmering\", \"Programmeringssprog\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"REST\", \"SOAP\"]','2025-06-30 11:24:48','2025-06-30 11:24:48'),(13,4250616207,'Senior Full Stack Engineer',13,'København, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nOnomondo is on a mission to revolutionize global IoT connectivity. Our AAA (App, API, And…) squad plays a crucial role in building and optimizing a reliable, secure, and scalable cellular network, empowering IoT businesses worldwide. We’re here to redefine how connected devices communicate, and we need great engineers to help us push the boundaries of what’s possible.\n\nWe are now hiring for an experienced Software Engineer for our AAA squad.\n\n\n\n\nThe AAA squad is a cross-functional group of engineers with unique and different backgrounds in software engineering, telco systems, embedded engineering and product management. Together, we are crafting the best cellular network in the world, built for the modern IoT landscape.\n\n\n\n\nOur work directly impacts millions of devices globally, ensuring seamless, low-latency, and highly available connectivity for mission-critical applications. Our services enable secure authentication, signaling and messaging for devices using Onomondo SIM cards, across 680+ networks in 180+ countries.\n\n\n\n\nYou will work with Kubernetes, Terraform, AWS, Grafana, Node.JS, Redis, and PostgreSQL. Ensuring the scalability and resilience of our core network.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWhat you’ll be doing\n\n\n\n\nAs a Senior Product Engineer in the AAA (App, API, And…) squad, you will be developing our web app, implementing and streamlining our backend, including our data ingestion pipeline, solving scaling, high availability, and observability challenges. The AAA squad is a team of 7 (2 x Product and 5 x Engineers). You will be reporting to Håkon Westh-Hansen, Engineering Manager.\n\n\n\n\nOur product is a lot more than a web app and a REST API though, and you will be able to apply your creativity to multiple tasks. You’ll be scaling a global cellular network serving millions of IoT devices, getting insights on everything that goes on from backend to frontend and much more.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nRequirements and Why We Need Your Skills!\n\n\n\n\nBuilding and maintaining backend services using Node.js, and debugging performance bottlenecks in high-throughput systems.\n\n\n\n\nDesigning and implementing data ingestion pipelines capable of handling millions of events per minute, while troubleshooting latency and scaling issues.\n\n\n\n\nWorking with React (and possibly Next.js) to create and debug front-end components that integrate seamlessly with backend APIs.\n\n\n\n\nWriting and optimizing complex SQL queries for PostgreSQL, and resolving data integrity or performance issues.\n\n\n\n\nNavigating and scripting in the command line to automate tasks and debug infrastructure or deployment problems.\n\n\n\n\nDeveloping and deploying applications using containerization technologies (e.g., Docker), and debugging container-related inconsistencies across environments.\n\n\n\n\nIntegrating and managing message queues like RabbitMQ, and resolving issues related to message delivery and system coordination.\n\n\n\n\nDesigning and maintaining scalable, secure, and highly available systems, while identifying and resolving system reliability or security concerns.\n\n\n\n\nImplementing and improving CI/CD pipelines using tools like GitHub Actions, and debugging build/test/deployment failures.\n\n\n\n\nSetting up and fine-tuning monitoring and logging systems (e.g., Prometheus, Grafana), and interpreting system metrics to diagnose issues.\n\n\n\n\nCollaborating closely with Product Managers, Designers, and Engineers to turn ideas into reliable, well-tested software.\n\n\n\n\nCommunicating technical decisions and collaborating effectively with teammates across the stack.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nComplementary skills\n\n\n\n\nYou\'ve worked in a high-growth SaaS company\nKnowledge of networking concepts and protocols\nExperience with telecom concepts\nExperience with building IoT solutions\nExperience with OTEL\nCKAD certification or a general interest in Kubernetes\nInterest in IaC, specifically Terraform/OpenTofu\nKnowledge in Zig or Golang\n\n\n\n\nWhy join Onomondo?\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nA playful, ambitious culture where people are trusted to do what they do best\nA workspace that’s one-of-a-kind, in both design and energy\nLegendary lunches, snack heaven, and events that actually bring people together\nRoom to bring your personality and ideas into the way we work and collaborate\n\n\n\n\nOur hiring process\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWe care deeply about creating a fair and inclusive process. That means:\n\nWe don’t need your picture or cover letter—just your CV\nWe select candidates based on skills and relevant work experience for the role.\n\nWe’re fast but thoughtful—our goal is to ensure you feel informed, respected, and excited throughout the journey.\n\n\n\n\n30-minute screening call with our recruiter, Christian Payne\nCode interview (in-person) with one of our Engineering Managers and an Engineer from the AAA (App, API, And…) squad.\nCulture Interview and Hire Manager Interview (1hr 20 mins). 30 mins with Mille Hertz (CPO) and a 50-minute interview with Dana (VP of Engineering)\nFinal stage - Meet our leadership for 30 minutes, onsite - Meet with our Co-Founder, Michael Karlsen and our CTO, Henrik Aagaard\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nReady to Make an Impact?\n\n\n\n\nPlease send us your CV, and let\'s start the conversation.\n\n\n\n\nLearn more about us and other opportunities at onomondo.com/careers','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4250616207/','2025-06-16',34,NULL,'[\"Kubernetes\", \"Node.js\", \"React.js\", \"SQL\", \"Data Ingestion\"]','2025-06-30 11:24:48','2025-06-30 11:24:48'),(14,4221263770,'IT-Projektmanager:in (m/w/d)',14,'Det Europæiske Økonomiske Samarbejdsområde','Om jobbet\n\nWas erwartet Sie?\n\nAufrechterhaltung und Weiterentwicklung unseres IT-Systems\nDatenbanken und deren Auswertung\nVerwaltung und Weiterentwicklung der Zahlungsschnittstellen\nProblemlösung und Neuprogrammierung von Infrastruktur-Elementen\nVerbesserung der internen Nutzungseffizienz\nSicherstellung der Systemstabilität\nVerbesserung der Schnittstellen und ihrer Dokumentation\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWas sollten Sie mitbringen\n\nSpaß am Kodieren und Probleme lösen\nDetailorientierte und strukturierte Arbeitsweise Verlässlichkeit und Belastbarkeit\nMindestens 2 Jahre relevante Berufserfahrung (idealerweise mit nachvollziehbarem Leistungsportfolio)\nTeam- und Kommunikationsfähigkeit\nUmfassende technische Kenntnisse in folgenden Aspekten: PHP Framework Laravel, AWS, Docker (weitere Kenntnisse sind von Vorteil\nDatenbanksysteme (MySQL, weitere Kenntnisse sind von Vorteil sowie\n\n APIs (REST, JSON, SOAP)Version Control (GIT) und Unit Testing\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWas bieten wir Ihnen\n\nFlache Hierarchien und die Möglichkeit, sich mit Ideen einzubringen\nEin agiles, hochprofessionelles, strebsames und wertschätzendes Arbeitsumfeld,\n\n Flexibilität und selbst bestimmtes Arbeiten\n\nArbeiten in einem stark wachsenden Unternehmen\nDie Möglichkeit, am Erfolg mitzuwirken und davon zu profitieren\nWettbewerbsfähige Vergütung\nGemeinsame Team-Events\nHochklassige Arbeitsausrüstung\nUmfangreiche Weiterbildungsmöglichkeiten','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4221263770/','2025-06-16',100,'Hybrid','[\"Backend-webudvikling\", \"Cloud Infrastructure\", \"Doctrine (PHP)\", \"Laravel\", \"MySQL\", \"PHP\", \"Softwarekonfigurationsledelse\", \"Webtjenester Amazon (AWS)\", \"Test af enheden\"]','2025-06-30 11:24:48','2025-06-30 11:24:48'),(15,4257009636,'SENIOR SOFTWARE ENGINEER',15,'København, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\n\n\n\n🚀 Join AltaPay and Help Shape the Future of PaymentsLooking for your next role in a global fintech company where innovation, agility, and impact go hand in hand?\n\nWelcome to AltaPay.\n\n💡 Who We Are\n\nHeadquartered in Copenhagen, AltaPay is a leading fintech company delivering state-of-the-art omni-channel payment solutions.\n\nWe help merchants across 22 European countries streamline reporting, ensure PCI-DSS compliance, and create seamless, engaging payment experiences for their customers. Our customer base is growing fast — and so is our ambition.\n\nReady to be part of something big? Keep reading 👇\n\n🔧 What You’ll Be Doing\n\nAs part of our agile engineering team, you’ll work at the heart of our core payment platform alongside passionate and skilled developers.\n\nDepending on your expertise, you could:\n\nIntegrate with a wide range of third-party APIs and protocols\nDevelop sleek, powerful interfaces for our partners and customers\nBuild and enhance our smart billing engine\nCreate intuitive self-service tools\nImprove our data pipeline and backend architecture\n\nYou’ll also:\n\nOwn all phases of the development lifecycle, from design to deployment\nPropose and implement innovative technical solutions\nEmbrace and promote software engineering best practices\nCollaborate with our DevOps team to automate and secure the deployment process\nContribute to the stability, scalability, and performance of our platform\n🧠 Who We’re Looking For\n\nYou’re more than a developer — you’re a problem-solver, a team player, and someone who genuinely cares about building high-quality software.\n\nWe think you’ll thrive here if you:\n\nHave 4–5+ years of experience as a software engineer\n\nAre fluent in PHP or Java, and understand design patterns deeply\n\nWork comfortably in Unix-like environments\n\nHave experience with relational and/or NoSQL databases\n\nAre quick to pick up new languages and tools when needed\n\nHave a pragmatic mindset with a strong focus on automation\n\nCan understand and simplify complex systems\n\nBonus points if you:\n\nHave hands-on experience with Java 11+, Docker, Kubernetes, Elastic, AWS or Serverless\n\nHave worked with payment providers (Visa, MasterCard, PayPal, MobilePay…)\n\nHave a passion for Machine Learning\n\nCome from an Agile/Scrum background and live by that mindset\n\n🎁 What We Offer\n\nAt AltaPay, we believe great work starts with a great environment.\n\nA key role in an ambitious fintech company with real impact\n\nA diverse and inclusive team (we speak 12+ languages!)\n\nA relaxed, down-to-earth atmosphere where collaboration matters\n\nFlexible working hours and the option to work from home\n\nCompetitive salary, pension plan, gym membership, massage perks & more\n\n🤝 Meet the Team\n\nWe’re a group of tech enthusiasts, problem-solvers, and collaborators. We take our work seriously — but not ourselves. Expect regular laughs, knowledge-sharing, and the occasional social event (yes, the dress code is casual – even at the party).\n\nAt AltaPay, diversity isn’t a buzzword — it’s our strength.\nWe celebrate differences, support inclusivity, and create space for everyone to thrive. No matter who you are, you’re welcome here.\n\n✨ Join us – and let’s build the future of payments together.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4257009636/','2025-06-28',NULL,NULL,'[\"Docker\", \"Java\", \"Kubernetes\", \"Linux\", \"OOP\", \"Scrum\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Webtjenester Amazon (AWS)\", \"NoSQL\", \"Problemløsning\"]','2025-06-30 11:25:41','2025-06-30 11:25:41'),(16,4250818692,'DevOps Softwareudviklere til PET og den gode sags tjeneste',16,'København, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nHar du lyst til at arbejde med videreudvikling af missionskritiske analyseapplikationer? Har du mod på at tilegne dig viden inden for et nyt teknisk felt? Og vil du have et job i en organisation, hvor hverdagen aldrig bliver hverdag? Så er du måske vores nye DevOps Softwareudvikler\n\nBliv en del af arbejdet med at sikre udviklingen af PET’s analyseværktøjer\n\nSom softwareudvikler i vores sektion for dataplatform og dataanalyse bliver din opgave bl.a. at bidrage til udviklingen af dataplatform og analyseværktøjer til vores operative analytikere. Teamet arbejder agilt og har ben i alle grene af PET, og du kommer derfor til at se et væld af spændende og varierende analysebehov med vidt forskellige formål. Vi er en del af centeret for applikationer og du vil indgå i et tæt samarbejde med centerets andre softwareudviklere, data scientists, data engineers og forretningsejere\n\nDataplatformsteamet står for at samle og udstille al PET’s operative data og har et tæt samarbejde med særligt indhentningsafdelingen. Da teamet er et centralt bindeled mellem indhentning og analyse, er det også et af de steder IT-udviklere kommer tættest på operationsmiljøet.\n\nAnalyseplatformsteamet er ansvarligt for at operative data kan arbejdes med i en analysekontekst på tværs af datakilder. Det er grundfundamentet for PET’s analysekapaciteter, og du har derfor et tæt samarbejde med analytikere og systemejere om alt fra nye dataintegrationer til ontologi og behovet for nye analysefunktionaliteter.\n\nDu kommer til at indgå i et dedikeret og unikt team med flad struktur, og får derved stor mulighed for medbestemmelse og indflydelse i dagligdagen. Vi har et uformelt arbejdsmiljø, hvor tillid, samarbejde og professionalisme er de væsentligste værdier.\n\nVi tilbyder dig en række spændende udviklingsopgaver på en dynamisk arbejdsplads med en operativ virkelighed, som du kommer helt tæt på. Du kommer til at arbejde med dygtige og professionelle kolleger med et højt fagligt niveau og meget stort engagement.\n\nFå en hverdag, der aldrig bliver hverdag\n\nDet kræver IT-profiler at værne om frihed, mennesker og demokrati og PET er en stor IT-arbejdsplads. Her arbejder Java-udviklere, infrastrukturspecialister, netværksteknikere, autodidakte hackere, firewallspecialister og mange andre med en baggrund inden for IT. Nogle har valgt PET for at arbejde med store og komplekse opgaver. Andre faldt for, at vi selv designer mange af vores løsninger fra bunden, udvikler og implementerer dem. Vores kollegaer skal bruge vores arbejde, og vi er med fra start til slut. Endelig har mange af os valgt jobbet for at arbejde med en sag, der er større end profit og timefakturering. Vi har et højere formål.\n\nVores arbejdsplads er som ingen andre. Som DevOps Softwareudvikler i PET bliver du en del af en hverdag, der er præget af opgaver, som ikke findes andre steder, og hver dag byder på nye udfordringer, som ikke fandtes i går. Vi har en hverdag, der aldrig bliver hverdag, og det kan du også få.\n\nDu kommer med en erfaring inden for IT og har mod på at angribe komplekse opgaver inden for et nyt felt\n\nVi ser gerne, at du har nogle års erfaring fra en fuldtidsstilling, og en uddannelse inden for IT, eksempelvis datamatiker eller anden relevant akademisk uddannelse. Det kan også være, at du har en uddannelse, hvor IT har spillet en stor rolle, eller at du er autodidakt med mindst tre års relevant erhvervserfaring.\n\nDet en fordel, hvis du har erfaring med, eller kendskab til, flere af nedenstående punkter:\n\n\n Linux\n Java applikationer\n Databaser (f.eks. PostgreSQL, Open Search)\n Docker, Kubernetes\n Asynkrone services og REST-API’er\n Webteknologier (F.eks. React)\n Automatiserede tests\n\n\nDet er ikke et krav, at du har kendskab til alle nævnte discipliner, men vi har en forventning om, at du kommer med en vilje til videreudvikle dig og har et gå-på-mod til at angribe komplekse opgaver, som kræver, at man skal tilegne sig viden på et nyt teknisk felt.\n\nI PET vægter vi desuden visse personlige kompetencer højt. Det er kompetencer, som vi mener, er essentielle for alle PET-ansatte uanset faglig baggrund. Det gør vi, fordi det er vigtigt for os, at vi finder det rette match. Du kan læse om kompetencerne her www.pet.dk/job.\n\nAnsættelsesforhold\n\nAnsættelsesstart pr 1. oktober eller 1. november - alternativt efter aftale. Vi forventer at påbegynde samtaler i uge 33. Du kan læse mere om hele PET’s ansættelsesproces på www.pet.dk/job.\n\nEt ansættelsesforhold i PET skal behandles med diskretion, hvilket du som ansøger skal være opmærksom på. Det betyder, at du som udgangspunkt godt kan fortælle tætte og fortrolige relationer, som du har tillid til, at du har søgt en stilling i PET, men ikke hvad jobbet indebærer.\n\nDet er en forudsætning for ansættelse i PET, at du kan sikkerhedsgodkendes til yderst hemmeligt, ligesom du skal kunne opretholde sikkerhedsgodkendelsen gennem hele din ansættelse. Som sikkerhedsgodkendt forventes det, at du er særlig opmærksom på din tavshedspligt i forhold til klassificeret information.\n\nHar du en akademisk baggrund, bliver du ansat på overenskomstvilkår i henhold til de til enhver tid gældende aftaler mellem Finansministeriet og Akademikernes Centralorganisation. Har du en anden uddannelsesmæssig baggrund, bliver du ansat på overenskomstvilkår i henhold til den til enhver tid gældende organisationsaftale for kontorfunktionærer i staten mellem Finansministeriet og HK/STAT samt OAO-S-fællesoverenskomst. Alternativt bliver du ansat på anden relevant overenskomst.\n\nDit arbejdssted bliver på Klausdalsbrovej 1 i Søborg, lige ved siden af Buddinge station, hvor både S-tog og bus kører lige til døren. I PET arbejder vi på interne systemer og med fortrolige opgaver, og derfor møder vi også på arbejde hver dag for at løse vores opgaver.\n\nYderligere information\n\nDu kan lære meget mere om PET som arbejdsplads på www.pet.dk/job, hvor du bl.a. kan læse mere om alle de fagligheder, der arbejder i PET og deres hverdag. Du kan også lytte til vores podcastserie ’Tjenesten og truslerne’.\n\nDu er også altid meget velkommen til at kontakte os på hverdage på mail hr-rekruttering@politi.dk eller på telefon +45 24 62 18 45, hvis du har spørgsmål til stillingen, PET som arbejdsplads eller lignende.\n\nNår du søger en stilling hos PET, giver du lov til, at vi må indhente dit CPR-nummer via CPR-registeret med henblik på identifikation af dig i forbindelse med rekrutteringsprocessen. Vi indhenter dit CPR-nummer, så vi sikkert kan fremsende relevante og nødvendige dokumenter til dig via Digital Post.\n\nDet er vigtigt for os, at PET afspejler den mangfoldighed, som vi arbejder for. Derfor opfordrer vi alle interesserede, uanset køn, alder, religion, seksualitet og etniske tilhørsforhold til at søge stillingen.\n\nTræd ind i en lukket verden, der åbner nye døre, hvor vi udvikler os, træner og bygger videre på det, vi kan. Om vi udvikler nye systemer, analyserer data eller finjusterer fodstillingen til skydetræning, så er vi altid på tæerne. Det skaber gode muligheder for, at du kan rykke dig med os, vokse med opgaverne og åbne nye døre i dit arbejdsliv.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4250818692/','2025-06-23',25,NULL,'[\"DevOps\", \"Java\", \"Kubernetes\", \"Linux\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Styresystemer\", \"Webteknologier\", \"Testautomatisering\"]','2025-06-30 11:25:41','2025-06-30 11:25:41'),(17,4250278837,'Backend Software Developer',17,'København, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nIf you are passionate about cloud software development, team collaboration, and creating outstanding backend code, join Spirii’s fantastic growth journey to lead the way for a sustainable future.\n\nSpirii develops and provides world-class charging products and digital solutions to customers with electric cars. Our Digital Development department is proud to drive a listen, learn, and lead culture that allows us to constantly improve our ways of working.\n\nAs a back-end Software Developer, you will be part of a team responsible for building a reliable and flexible charging experience for EV drivers, both professional drivers and private individuals. You will report to an Engineering Manager and work closely with CPH and near-shore colleagues in the product development team and our external partners.\n\nWhat You Will Do\n\nTogether with your team, you will be responsible for:\n\n\nDesigning, building, and maintaining scalable backend services using Node.js, NestJS, and TypeScript \nCollaborate closely with mobile frontend developers to support seamless integration with the React Native application \nContribute to architectural decisions and solution design for cloud-native, distributed systems \nDriving the adoption of automated testing, including unit, integration, and load testing \nEnsuring quality of releases and best practice coding standards \nParticipate in code reviews and provide constructive feedback to peers \n\n\nWho You Are\n\n\nLike to explore innovative technologies and continuously expand your skills \nAmbitious on behalf of our customers, our company and yourself, whilst focusing on excellent execution. \nHave a high sense of ownership in your work and actively maintain operational awareness \nA passion for delivering high quality, cloud-native software solutions. \nCare about how your work and attitude affect those who are around you - you are an active participant not only in feature creation but in creating an open and friendly environment in the team. \nComfortable working in agile, cross-functional teams that include mobile and full-stack developers \nExcellent English communication skills and ability to interact with all levels in an organization – internally and externally with partners/customers. \n\n\nQualifications\n\n\nBachelor\'s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field (or equivalent experience). \n5+ years of professional software development experience. \nExperience with the server-side aspects of mobile app development is preferred. \nKnowledge of Elasticsearch, Redis, and non-SQL databases is an advantage \nMobile development principles and tools (React Native experience is a plus) \nStrong experience with: \nTypeScript or JavaScript (Node.js, NestJS) \nCloud-based microservice architecture \nBuilding high-performing back-end architecture \nCloud platforms such as AWS \nHands-on experience with test-driven development, test automation, integration and load testing. \nIntegration between external & internal IT systems \nAPI design \nExperience with the implementation of EV Charging Industry, OCPI-OICP or other protocols is an advantage. \n\n\nBenefits\n\nIt is important for us to create a healthy, diverse, fun, and creative working environment, so besides all the basic benefits, we also focus a lot on social activities, flexible working hours and a good work life balance.\n\n\nFlexible Work Environment: Enjoy a collaborative, inclusive, and open workplace designed to fit your needs and support work-life balance.\nCompetitive Package: A competitive salary, an 11% company pension plan, and a comprehensive benefits package.\nTime to Recharge: Benefit from 32 paid vacation days and paid parental leave to focus on what matters most.\nCareer Growth: Access professional development opportunities and grow your career in a high-impact, high-growth industry.\nStay Energized: Enjoy excellent coffee, tea, free snacks, and subsidized lunches at the office.\nStay Active: Use our Spirii gym and shared company car to keep moving.\nMake an Impact: Be part of a team driving the future of sustainable energy while working on meaningful projects.\nTwo innovation days per month for YOU to choose what you work on.\n\n\nThe position is a permanent position in Copenhagen, Denmark. Danish language is not a requirement, but Fluent English language skills are required.\n\nAbout Spirii – Who We Are\n\nSpirii is a full-service e-Mobility provider, which offers hardware and software charging solutions to companies in the private and the public sector. Spirii has recently celebrated its four-year anniversary as a founded company, however the people in Spirii have extensive experience working with electric cars and charging, as well as development of future transport- and energy systems.\n\nSpirii is an equal opportunity employer. We encourage applications from candidates of all backgrounds and experiences. Spirii strives to create an inclusive and diverse workplace, and we encourage all qualified applicants to apply regardless of age, gender, race, sexual/religious orientation, or disability','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4250278837/','2025-06-16',NULL,NULL,'[\"Backend-webudvikling\", \"Datalogi\", \"JavaScript\", \"Microservices\", \"OOP\", \"React.js\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Udvikling af mobilapps\", \"Webtjenester Amazon (AWS)\", \"Testautomatisering\"]','2025-06-30 11:25:41','2025-06-30 11:25:41'),(18,4256729856,'Webbutvecklare med CMS-erfarenhet',18,'Malmø, Skåne len, Sverige','Om jobbet\n\nVi söker en nyfiken problemlösare och lagspelare med öga för kvalitet. Du trivs i nära samarbete med kollegor, stöttar juniora utvecklare och tar gärna en ledarroll vid behov. Hos Advania Development skapar vi digitala lösningar som ger verkligt kundvärde i en innovativ och flexibel arbetsmiljö, där du får utvecklas inom webbutveckling.\n\nWebbutvecklare på Advania 🚀\n\nSom webbutvecklare hos oss blir du en viktig del av vårt utvecklingsteam. Du samarbetar tätt med utvecklare, designers, produktägare och affärsutvecklare för att ta fram nya, långsiktiga och användarvänliga digitala lösningar.\n\nArbetsuppgifter:\n\nSkapa och vidareutveckla webblösningar med hög användbarhet och tillgänglighet\n\nBygga och förvalta webapps baserade på kunders behov och önskemål\n\nFelsöka, åtgärda problem och proaktivt stödja kunder i samarbete med förvaltningsledare\n\nArbeta i moderna tekniker, plattformar och verktyg för CMS, exempelvis Sitevision, Optimizely eller Umbraco\n\nHålla dig uppdaterad om aktuella tekniker, säkerhetskrav (NIS2) och tillgänglighetsstandarder (WCAG)\nVad vi söker hos dig ✨\n\nFör att du ska trivas och passa hos oss söker vi dig som har en bakgrund inom webbutveckling med fokus på CMS-lösningar och/eller systemutveckling. Du arbetar idag i en roll som webbutvecklare, systemutvecklare eller kanske som fullstackutvecklare med erfarenhet av moderna tekniker och plattformar. \n\nVi söker dig som har:\n\nMinst några års erfarenhet av webbutveckling i CMS-produkter som Sitevision, Optimizely eller Umbraco.\n.NET, JavaScript, CSS, HTML, React, TypeScript, C# och SQL\nCertifikationer inom Sitevision, Umbraco och/eller Optimizely\nVi ser fram emot din ansökan! 👋\n\nVisa gärna ditt intresse så snart som möjligt då vi intervjuar löpande. Vi välkomnar sökanden med olika bakgrunder, erfarenheter och synsätt, eftersom vi vet att en bredare mångfald berikar var och en av oss och stärker såväl effektivitet som kreativitet i vårt arbete.\n\nSom en del av vår rekryteringsprocess genomgår våra slutkandidater en obligatorisk bakgrundskontroll, en för oss kvalitativ kontroll inför ett anställningsbeslut. Advania samarbetar även med Ljung & Sjöberg för en proaktiv arbetsplats kopplat till alkohol och droger.\n\nTveka inte att höra av dig om du har några frågor eller funderingar.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4256729856/','2025-06-27',NULL,NULL,'[\"Backend-webudvikling\", \"CSS\", \"Frontend-udvikling\", \"HTML\", \"HTML5\", \"JavaScript\", \"OOP\", \"React.js\", \"Webudvikling\", \"Samarbejde\"]','2025-06-30 11:25:41','2025-06-30 11:25:41'),(19,4031923300,'Software Developer',19,'København og omegn','Om jobbet\n\nStillingsbeskrivelse\n\nVil du være med til at udvikle nogle af branchens vigtigste og mest komplekse IT-løsninger? Som Software Developer i Netcompany vil du være med til at gøre en mærkbar forskel for både vores offentlige og private kunder.\n\nArbejdsopgaver og teknologi\n\nSom Software Developer vil du blive en del af vores Netcompany Application Services, der består af en fast teamstruktur, der driver porteføljer af spændende kunder og projekter. Din hverdag vil være præget af både tekniske og kunderettede opgaver med leverancer, der spænder fra nyudvikling af IT-projekter til løbende udvikling på eksisterende løsninger og serviceydelser.\n\nI Netcompany leverer vi på alle markedsudbredte teknologier herunder .Net, C#, Java, Salesforce, Sharepoint, Dynamics CRM, Business Central ERP, Sitecore, ReactJS, Angular, Docker, Azure, Azure DevOps, Octopus, Oracle, Episerver m.fl. Valget af teknologi bestemmes altid efter, hvad der giver kunden størst værdi. Det er derfor vigtigt, at du synes, det er sjovt at arbejde med nye og varierende områder og teknologier samt finder det motiverende at udbygge din viden kontinuerligt.\n\nDine arbejdsopgaver kan bl.a. indebære:\n\n\nKundedialog og behovsafklaring\nImplementering af funktioner i brugergrænsefladen\nProgrammering af frontend og backend til nye features i kundens løsninger\nOpsætning og udvikling af frameworks samt integrationer\nKonfiguration og udvikling af extensions til standardplatforme\nAutomatisering af forretningsprocesser i form af f.eks. batchjobs\n\n\nOm dig\n\nVi forestiller os, at du er universitetsuddannet bachelor eller diplomingeniør inden for eksempelvis datalogi, software, IT eller lignende. Derudover forestiller vi os, at du:\n\n\nEr nyuddannet eller har et par års erfaring - vigtigst er, at du brænder for at tage din karriere inden for IT til næste niveau\nBesidder gode IT-tekniske kompetencer inden for objektorienteret programmering\nHar et analytisk og problemløsende mindset, der gør dig i stand til at løse komplekse og tekniske opgaver for vores kunder\n\n\nFortsæt din udvikling hos os\n\nI Netcompany har vi fokus på din personlige og faglige udvikling.\n\nNår du starter hos os, får du en personlig mentor, som vil vejlede dig igennem din udvikling og i at nå dine mål. Den tætte relation til en erfaren kollega er med til at sikre trivsel for den enkelte medarbejder og giver dig samtidig konkret indblik i de mange forskellige karrieremuligheder, efterhånden som du opbygger din erfaring.\n\nDerudover deltager du i vores uddannelsesprogram, Netcompany Academy, hvor du tilbydes kurser og seminarer, om alt fra teknologier til kundehåndtering. Alle kurser undervises af erfarne Netcompany kolleger, hvilket er med til at sikre, at alt indhold er af høj relevans og bygger ovenpå din faglighed, så du bliver godt klædt på til at varetage forskellige opgaver og hele tiden dygtiggør dig gennem din karriere hos os.\n\nBliv en del af et inkluderende fællesskab\n\nI Netcompany prioriterer vi fællesskab højt. Vi fremmer aktivt en åben og imødekommende arbejdskultur, der bygger på samarbejde og tillid til hinanden, og hvor der altid er mulighed for sparring.\n\nDet er en del af vores kultur og værdigrundlag, at alle medarbejdere, uanset baggrund, identitet og erfaring mødes med forståelse og respekt samt lige muligheder for udvikling og trivsel.\n\nDu får mulighed for at opnå læring og samarbejde med kolleger på tværs af kulturer og nationaliteter, da vi som international virksomhed har kontorer i mange lande.\n\nVi tilbyder et fælles miljø, hvor vi engagerer os i hinanden på tværs af afdelinger og projekter. Hertil har vi en lang række af sociale og faglige arrangementer, der giver dig de bedste muligheder for at udvide og opbygge et netværk allerede tidligt i din karriere.\n\nSend os en ansøgning \n\nUpload dit CV og en motiveret ansøgning til vores rekrutteringssystem via linket. Har du ikke fået svar på alle dine spørgsmål, er du velkommen til at skrive til hr.dk@netcompany.com\n\nAlle kvalificerede kandidater opfordres til at søge uanset køn, kønsudtryk, seksualitet, handicap, alder, religion og tro, politisk anskuelse, nationalitet, etnicitet eller sociale baggrund.\n\nVi er engagerede i at skabe et inkluderende og mangfoldigt miljø. Vores rekrutteringsprocesser er baseret på individuel merit. Hvis du har behov for tilpasninger eller ekstra støtte under ansættelsesprocessen, bedes du sende en e-mail til vores ansvarlige rekrutteringsmedarbejdere på reasonableadjustmentsdk@netcompany.com for hjælp.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4031923300/','2025-06-23',100,NULL,'[\".NET\", \"Angular\", \"Backend-webudvikling\", \"Java\", \"JavaScript\", \"OOP\", \"Programmering\", \"Programmeringssprog\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Styresystemer\"]','2025-06-30 11:25:41','2025-06-30 11:25:41'),(20,4253125019,'Full Stack Developer (Frontend Focus) for Lab Digitalization Project - DTU Chemical Engineering',20,'Kongens Lyngby, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nJob Description\n\nAre you passionate about building intuitive and engaging web applications that transform the way scientists work in laboratories? Do you have a solid foundation in React development, JavaScript/TypeScript, and an interest in interdisciplinary collaboration? Then join us at DTU Chemical Engineering and help shape the future of laboratory digitalization!\n\nThe job\n\nThe position will be anchored in the Hempel Foundation Coatings Science and Technology Research Center (CoaST), spanning the entire value chain of industrial coatings R&D. To virtually visit the state-of-the-art labs that are at the center of the digitalization project, visit https://virtual.kt.dtu.dk/CoaST-labs/ . You will be at the heart of our ambitious project to develop a robust, user-friendly web interface designed to streamline laboratory workflows, experiment tracking, and data management. Working closely with scientists and users, you will ensure that our React-based platform meets their needs effectively, encouraging widespread adoption and making a tangible impact on research efficiency and collaboration. The digitalization project also includes integration with our maritime field test station in Hundested Harbour, supporting experimental activities under natural exposure conditions that complement laboratory-based studies.\n\nOur software ecosystem includes a React frontend connected via a FastAPI backend to a PostgreSQL database, all deployed seamlessly on Kubernetes using CI/CD pipelines. While your primary role will focus on front-end development, we encourage and support professional growth across the full stack, tailored specifically to your interests and skills.\n\nResponsibilities And Qualifications\n\nYou will be responsible for developing and refining a user-friendly React frontend, pivotal for ensuring laboratory researchers can efficiently specify experiments, manage and upload data, and streamline their workflow. You will collaborate closely with end-users from a highly international team with diverse academic and cultural backgrounds, gathering feedback to continuously improve usability and performance. You should enjoy open communication and value interdisciplinary teamwork. An understanding or background in chemical engineering would be advantageous, as it will facilitate effective communication and alignment with laboratory users.\n\nYour primary responsibilities will include:\n\n\nDesigning, developing, and maintaining a responsive and intuitive React-based frontend\nIntegrate the React frontend with REST APIs designed with FastAPI\nWriting and maintaining clear, professional documentation to ensure long-term maintainability and knowledge transfer\nCollaborating with lab users to clearly define their needs and continuously refine the user experience\nImplementing rigorous testing procedures to ensure software reliability and user satisfaction\nDeploying and managing applications using Kubernetes and CI/CD pipelines via GitLab\n\n\nEssential skills:\n\n\nSolid experience in React and JavaScript/TypeScript\nExperience in web application development and integrating React with REST APIs\nKnowledge of OpenAPI standards \nProficiency in Python for backend interactions and data processing\nFundamental knowledge of SQL databases\nFamiliarity with software testing methodologies and frameworks like Jest, Junit, pytest etc\nExperience with Git and containerized applications (Docker)\n\n\nAdditional beneficial skills include:\n\n\nBackground or basic understanding of chemical engineering or similar fields\nExperience with Kubernetes, FastAPI, PostgreSQL, or similar backend technologies\nAgile or Scrum project management practices\nSetting up and maintaining CI/CD pipelines for deployment in Kubernetes\nFamiliarity with authentication, authorization and user management.\n\n\nJoin us to create impactful software solutions that drive innovation and user engagement at the forefront of scientific research.\n\nFormal Qualifications\n\nYou should hold a relevant degree at the Bachelor’s or Master’s level in computer science, software engineering, information technology, or a similar technical field. Applicants with degrees in other STEM disciplines and documented experience in frontend development are also encouraged to apply.\n\nWe offer\n\nDTU is a leading technical university globally recognized for the excellence of its research, education, innovation and scientific advice. We offer a rewarding and challenging job in an international environment. We strive for academic excellence in an environment characterized by collegial respect and academic freedom tempered by responsibility.\n\nSalary and appointment terms \n\nThe appointment will be based on the collective agreement with the Danish Confederation of Professional Associations (AC).\n\nApplication and contact\n\nPlease submit your online application no later than 16 July 2025 (23:59 Danish time). Open the “Apply now” link, fill out the form and attach your motivated application, CV and exam certificates.\n\nIf you would like additional information about the position, please contact Associate Professor Jochen Dreyer ( jodre@kt.dtu.dk ).\n\nYou can read more about DTU Chemical Engineering and CoaST at www.kt.dtu.dk/english and https://www.kt.dtu.dk/research/coast, respectively. To take a virtual tour of the CoaST labs, visit https://virtual.kt.dtu.dk/CoaST-labs/.\n\nApplications received after the deadline will not be considered.\n\nAll interested candidates irrespective of age, gender, disability, race, religion or ethnic background are encouraged to apply. As DTU works with research in critical technology, which is subject to special rules for security and export control, open-source background checks may be conducted on qualified candidates for the position.\n\nThe Hempel Foundation Coatings Science and Technology Centre (CoaST) was established at the Technical University of Denmark, DTU, as per 1 January 2017, based on a generous donation by the Hempel Foundation. CoaST Research Centre supports the development, production and use of high-performance organic coatings. Working along the whole value chain, CoaST research activities cover organic, polymer-based coating technologies from raw materials over formulation, test and characterization to production and application.\n\nThe Department of Chemical and Biochemical Engineering at DTU is a leader in innovative teaching and research, built on core technical subjects and engineering scientific disciplines. The teaching and research cover separation processes, reaction engineering, dynamics and process regulation, process and facility planning, unit operations, heat transmission, fluid mechanics and applied thermodynamics. The Department enjoys very close relations with international partners, and especially a wide range of industrial companies. \n\nTechnology for people\n\nDTU develops technology for people. With our international elite research and study programmes, we are helping to create a better world and to solve the global challenges formulated in the UN’s 17 Sustainable Development Goals. Hans Christian Ørsted founded DTU in 1829 with a clear mission to develop and create value using science and engineering to benefit society. That mission lives on today. DTU has 13,500 students and 6,000 employees. We work in an international atmosphere and have an inclusive, evolving, and informal working environment. DTU has campuses in all parts of Denmark and in Greenland, and we collaborate with the best universities around the world.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4253125019/','2025-06-23',100,NULL,'[\"Datalogi\", \"Frontend-udvikling\", \"Git\", \"JavaScript\", \"React.js\", \"SQL\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Databaser\", \"Kemiingeniørarbejde\", \"Termodynamik\"]','2025-06-30 11:25:41','2025-06-30 11:25:41'),(21,4251652650,'Technology Consultant',21,'København og omegn','Om jobbet\n\nAre you passionate about designing and developing cutting-edge solutions that drive organizational success? Do you thrive in a dynamic environment where no two days are the same? We are looking for talents in both Copenhagen, Aarhus and Oslo.\n\n\n\n\nAt DYNACAP, we are looking for a talented Technology Consultant to join our team. In this role, you will take on diverse responsibilities, including solution design, development, configuration, testing, project management, and customer collaboration. You will have a direct impact on our clients’ success while working closely with an ambitious, and collaborative team.\n\n\n\n\nWho we are\n\nDYNACAP is a hands-on transformation partner, helping ambitious companies optimize commercial operations, exclusively through Salesforce, the world’s #1 CRM platform. Founded in 2020, we are a fast-growing team of 50+ ambitious experts working in a diverse culture, where commercial specialists develop a clear understanding of technology, and technical experts\n\nlearn to grasp the commercial requirements and business objectives. We thereby bridge the often- overlooked gap between business and technology, satisfying both. This is what we mean by dynamic capabilities. It’s our name. It’s our strength.\n\n\n\n\nWe see ambitions as the spark for growth – for individuals and businesses. We create environments that inspire and empower, making it possible to turn bold ideas into transformative\n\nresults.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nCollaborate with clients to create business requirements and functional designs\nDesign and automate business processes to optimize commercial operations\nPerform data modeling and database design for scalable solutions\nDevelop commercial solutions for sales, marketing, and service teams\nDesign and implement integrations using cloud technologies\nProvide best-practice advice from both technical and commercial perspectives to top management\nSupport customers in their digital transformation by designing and implementing tailored solutions\n\n\n\n\nIdeally you\n\nHold a Master’s degree in Computer Science & Engineering, Data Science, Business Administration & Information Systems, or a similar field\nThrive in a fast-paced, collaborative environment while maintaining a strong work ethic\nHave experience with object-oriented programming and knowledge of database design\nAre knowledgeable about or interested in customer-facing systems\nAre eager to take responsibility both internally and with customers\n\n\n\n\nWhat we offer\n\nOpportunities for accelerated career development in a dynamic and supportive environment\nWork with cutting-edge technology on transformative projects\nCollaborate with top management and technical specialists to solve key strategic challenges for our clients\nExtensive responsibility and freedom to shape your role\nCompetitive salary and benefits package\nBe part of a unique culture that encourages collaboration, social engagement, and a strong sense of belonging\n\n\n\n\nWant to join us?\n\nPlease submit your cover letter, CV, and academic transcripts (bachelor’s and master’s).\n\nWe are hiring on a rolling basis and would love for you to start as soon as possible.\n\n\n\n\nIf you have any questions, feel free to contact Caroline Bjerre Andersen, Head of Talent Acquisition, People & Culture, at newtalent@dynacap.com.\n\n\n\n\nJoin us in empowering ambitions.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWe look forward to hearing from you!','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4251652650/','2025-06-23',54,NULL,'[\"Datalogi\", \"CRM\", \"Data-arkitektur\", \"Databasedesign\", \"Datamodellering\", \"Informationsystemer\", \"Rådgivning\", \"Salesforce.com\", \"Technical Solution Design\"]','2025-06-30 11:25:41','2025-06-30 11:25:41'),(22,4249161535,'Projektleder',22,'Solrød Strand, Region Sjælland, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nProjektleder til Thorslev Automation ApS\n\n\n\n\nEr du typen, der drømmer i projektplaner og vågner op med en færdig risikomatrix i hovedet? Og vil du være med til at forme fremtiden i en virksomhed, hvor man godt må grine – også når der er travlt?\n\n\n\n\nSå læs videre!\n\n\n\n\nHos Thorslev Automation leder vi efter en projektleder, der kan holde styr på vores spændende og komplekse automationsprojekter – uden at miste overblikket eller humoren. Vi er eksperter i PLC/HMI, SCADA og styretavler, men mangler dig til at holde det hele på sporet.\n\nDin hverdag vil blandt andet bestå af:\n\n\n\n\n· At få projekter til at køre glat – både teknisk og menneskeligt\n\n· At samarbejde tæt med Carsten, der er vores flinke daglige leder\n\n· At sikre kvalitet, kundetilfredshed og fremdrift – uden at miste smilet\n\n· At videreudvikle vores projektmodel (ja, vi har en – og den bliver bedre hver dag)\n\n\n\n\nVi forestiller os, at du:\n\n· Har 5+ års erfaring med projektledelse i industrien\n\n· Har styr på PRINCE2 (eller lignende), og gerne noget teknisk viden\n\n· Ikke bliver nervøs ved tanken om Excel, GanttPro eller SCADA (eller kolleger med stærke meninger)\n\n\n\n\nTil gengæld tilbyder vi:\n\n· En arbejdsplads med højt til loftet, stærkt fællesskab og plads til dig\n\n· Frokost i kantinen (dog med madpakke), fredagsbarer og gode grin\n\n· Løn efter kvalifikationer, pension, sundhedssikring og fleksibilitet\n\n\n\n\nStartdato: 1. september – eller når du er klar\n\nLokation: Solrød Strand (tæt på både strand og motorvej)\n\n\n\n\nEr du klar til at lede projekter, der batter – og gøre det med overskud og ordentlighed? Så send os din ansøgning, og lad os tage en snak. Vi glæder os!','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4249161535/','2025-06-16',29,NULL,'[\"Byggeledelse\", \"Byggeri\", \"Forhandling\", \"Kontraktstyring\", \"Microsoft Excel\", \"Programstyring\", \"Projektplanlægning\", \"Teamledelse\", \"Teamlederskab\", \"Ændringsstyring\"]','2025-06-30 11:26:29','2025-06-30 11:26:29'),(23,4248060909,'Driftsleder, Juli Living, København',23,'København, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nVi søger en erfaren og selvkørende driftsleder, der vil være med til at sikre, at vores ejendomme i København altid fremstår velholdte og fungerer optimalt.\n\n\n\n\nJuli Living er en selvstændig platform under Nrep, der er en af de førende ejendomsinvestorer og -innovatorer i Norden. Med en ambition om at forbedre livet for vores kunder, arbejder vi målrettet på at levere boliger af høj kvalitet og yde en høj personlig kundeservice. \n\n\n\n\nVi vil være tæt på vores kunder, og gøre en forskel på agendaen for social bæredygtighed. Det er helt afgørende, at du forstår og er i stand til at arbejde passioneret med tanken om, at kunden er vores vigtigste aktiv. Vi vil være dem med de bedste produkter og services, og her kommer du til at spille en vigtig rolle.\n\n\n\n\nTeamet\n\nVi søger en kollega, der kan arbejde selvstændigt, tage ansvar og sikre, at vores ejendomme er velholdte og velfungerende. Vi værdsætter et positivt mindset, gode samarbejdsevner og lysten til at sikre en høj standard for vores beboere.\n\n\n\n\nStillingen\n\nSom driftsleder vil du spille en vigtig rolle i den daglige drift af ejendommene. Dine opgaver vil blandt andet omfatte\n\n\n\n\nDagligt tilsyn og vedligeholdelse af ejendommene\nUdbedring af mindre reparationer og koordinering af eksterne håndværkere\nLøsning af tekniske udfordringer på bygninger og installationer\nKommunikation med beboere og håndtering af deres henvendelser\nTilsyn med fællesarealer, teknikrum og udendørsarealer\nBidrage til at sikre en stabil og effektiv drift af ejendommene\n\n\n\n\nKvalifikationer\n\nVi søger en driftsleder med erfaring fra nybyggeri og en god teknisk forståelse. Det er en fordel, hvis du har en håndværksmæssig baggrund som fx blikkenslager, elektriker eller tømrer, men det er ikke et krav.\n\n\n\n\nDu trives med at arbejde selvstændigt og tage ansvar for dine ejendomme. Samtidig er du serviceminded og klar til at hjælpe beboerne med små og store udfordringer i hverdagen. Du har desuden gode samarbejdsevner og kan kommunikere klart og venligt med beboere, kolleger og eksterne samarbejdspartnere.\n\n\n\n\nVi tilbyder\n\nVi tilbyder en spændende mulighed, for at blive en del af en ambitiøs virksomhed i et dynamisk team med godt samspil og stærke kompetencer. Et job hvor du får mulighed for at tage ansvar, arbejde selvstændigt og gøre en forskel for forretningen og vores kunder. Du vil blive en del af en hurtigt voksende afdeling med store ambitioner.\n\n\n\n\nSkriv til os\n\nSend din ansøgning og CV via ansøgningslinket hurtigst muligt og senest den 9. juli 2025. Vi har samtaler i ansøgningsperioden og ansætter så snart vi har fundet den rette kandidat. Har du spørgsmål, er du velkommen til at kontakte Head of Facility Management, Lukas Hummer, luhe@nrep.com. Vi afholder samtaler løbende, så send din ansøgning hurtigst muligt.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4248060909/','2025-06-16',44,NULL,'[\"Facility Management (FM)\"]','2025-06-30 11:26:30','2025-06-30 11:26:30'),(24,4252753355,'Senior Full-Stack Engineer (Typescript, React & PHP)',24,'Den Europæiske Union','Om jobbet\n\nAbout the company:\n\nAvenue Code is the leading software consultancy focused on delivering end-to-end development solutions for digital transformation across every vertical. We’re privately held, profitable, and have been on a solid growth trajectory since day one. We care deeply about our clients, our partners, and our people. We prefer the word ‘partner’ over ‘vendor’, and our investment in professional relationships is a reflection of that philosophy. We pride ourselves on our technical acumen, our collaborative problem-solving ability, and the warm professionalism of our teams.\n\n\n\n\nAvenue Code has been believing in and promoting plurality actions for over 10 years, understanding that recognizing differences and fostering a safe environment, employment opportunities, representation, and support are the best ways to promote an increasingly equitable culture.\n\n\n\n\nAbout The Opportunity\n\nWe are looking for a Senior Full Stack Engineer to join our clients internal engineering team and drive the development and modernization of their platform. This role blends strong front-end expertise with backend contributions and full project ownership.\n\nYou\'ll be a core part of a cross-functional squad delivering high-impact, user-facing features at scale and embedded in a fast-moving team of full stack engineers, a product manager, a designer, and a software developer in test (SDET) - with a strong focus on collaboration, shared ownership, and continuous delivery.\n\n\n\n\nResponsibilities\n\nDevelop and maintain features across both the frontend (TypeScript + React) and backend (PHP, Golang)\nBuild user interfaces with accessibility and performance in mind\nContribute to the modernization and migration of core systems and services\nParticipate in code reviews, pair programming and daily collaboration and agile ceremonies\nCollaborate cross-functionally with designers, product managers, and other engineers to ship impactful product updates\nTake ownership of key components in large projects and deliver them end-to-end\nSupport a culture of quality, empathy, and iterative improvement.\n\n\n\n\nRequired Qualifications\n\n5+ years of professional experience as a software engineer, ideally in full stack roles\nStrong proficiency in TypeScript and React.js\nBackend development experience in Golang & PHP\nA collaborative mindset and experience working in agile product teams\nExpected to be able to work flexible across both Frontend and Backend systems\nFamiliarity with accessibility best practices and modern frontend architecture\nComfortable working in highly communicative, remote-first environments\nStrong English communication skills (spoken and written)\n\n\n\n\nNice To Have Skills\n\nExperience with AWS and cloud-native application patterns\nFamiliarity with Angular.js (legacy support only)\nExposure to CI/CD tools and infrastructure automation such as GitHub Actions, Makefile, and Terraform\nA/B Testing frameworks, or experimentation tools: Libraries & SDKs Optimizely, Snowplow, Axios.\nPrevious experience in large-scale migrations or platform modernization initiatives.\n\n\n\n\nAvenue Code reinforces its commitment to privacy and to all the principles guaranteed by the most accurate global data protection laws, such as GDPR, LGPD, CCPA and CPRA. The Candidate data shared with Avenue Code will be kept confidential and will not be transmitted to disinterested third parties, nor will it be used for purposes other than the application for open positions. As a Consultancy company, Avenue Code may share your information with its clients and other Companies from the CompassUol Group to which Avenue Code’s consultants are allocated to perform its services.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4252753355/','2025-06-23',100,NULL,'[\"React.js\", \"Søg\", \"TypeScript\"]','2025-06-30 11:26:30','2025-06-30 11:26:30'),(25,4192173942,'Senior Webbutvecklare till Frontwalker i Malmö',25,'Malmø, Skåne len, Sverige','Om jobbet\n\nVi söker en senior Webbutvecklare till Frontwalker i Malmö, är det du?\n\nVi söker erfarna och engagerade utvecklare som vill bli en del av vårt team i Malmö. Hos oss får du möjlighet att arbeta med varierande uppdrag inom både offentlig och privat sektor. Här finns möjlighet att bidra i våra förvaltningsuppdrag som bedrivs inhouse och/eller spännande resursuppdrag ute hos kunder.\n\nOm rollen\n\nSom senior webbutvecklare hoppas vi att du vill ta ett stort ansvar för leveransen – från idé och koncept till implementation och färdig produkt, gärna i ett tätt samarbete med resten av teamet. Du har mångårig erfarenhet av att bygga modern webb från start till mål och en djup förståelse och nyfikenhet i arbetet med kunder. Du har relevanta kompetenser, kvalitetsmedveten och trivs bäst i nära samarbete med kollegor och kunder.\n\nDin kommunikativa förmåga gör att du tydligt kan förmedla lösningar och skapa affärsvärde genom att förstå kundens behov. Med en nyfikenhet för nya tekniska och affärsmässiga trender bidrar du aktivt till att utveckla både våra kunder och oss som bolag.\n\nVi letar efter dig som:\n\n\nHar minst 10 års erfarenhet av webbutveckling, gärna WordPress, moderna JavaScript-ramverk och PHP.\nHar erfarenhet av både frontend- och backendutveckling.\nStarkt meriterande och du arbetat som konsult tidigare.\nHar en stark förmåga att bygga långsiktiga relationer och leverera hög kvalitet.\nTar ansvar för hela leveranser och har en tydlig förståelse för kunders affärsbehov.\n\n\nOm Frontwalker\n\nFrontwalker är en växande IT-koncern med bred geografisk spridning i Sverige. Vi är idag 50+ anställda och finns på fyra orter i landet. Hos oss hittar du helt vanliga människor som dessutom är vassa inom systemutveckling, tillgänglighet, IT Management, kravanalys, test och mycket mer.\n\nVi arbetar både med inhouseprojekt på vårt kontor och ute hos våra kunders projekt som specialister. Våra uppdrag är ofta långsiktiga och vi har många kunder som vi har arbetat med i flera år. Vi gillar omväxlingen och kombination av förvaltning, nyutveckling och spännande resursuppdrag.\n\nVi erbjuder dig:\n\n\nEn inkluderande arbetsplats där vi värdesätter samarbete och trivsel.\nWork-life balance och flexibla arbetstider.\nInterna utvecklingsmöjligheter och kontinuerlig kompetensutveckling.\nMarknadsmässig lön och förmåner, inklusive friskvård och försäkringar.\nEtt varierat och utvecklande arbete där du kan bidra med din erfarenhet och kreativitet.\n\n\nHos oss ingår du i ett team med duktiga kollegor och får möjlighet att arbeta i projekt som spänner över allt från myndigheter till privat näringsliv. Vi strävar efter att ha kul på jobbet och att hela tiden utvecklas tillsammans!\n\nVill du vara en Frontwalker?\n\nVad väntar du på? Skicka in din ansökan så snart som möjligt då urval sker löpande. Vid frågor om rekryteringen är du välkommen att kontakta Carolina Gustavson på 073 505 42 34 eller mejla till rekrytering@frontwalker.se Varmt välkommen att höra av dig!','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4192173942/','2025-03-30',NULL,NULL,'[\"AJAX\", \"CSS\", \"HTML\", \"HTML5\", \"JavaScript\", \"OOP\", \"PHP\", \"React.js\", \"Webudvikling\", \"WordPress\"]','2025-06-30 11:26:30','2025-06-30 11:26:30'),(26,4240246619,'Applikationsspecialister til en hverdag, der aldrig bliver hverdag i PET',26,'København, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nKunne du tænke dig at levere systemer og applikationer til en organisation, som ikke ligner nogle andre? Er automatisering af driftsprocesser en central del af din værktøjskasse? Og kan du spænde over både legacy og nyudviklede applikationer? Så er du måske vores nye applikationsspecialist i Center for Applikationer.\n\nBliv en del af arbejdet med at modernisere applikationslandskabet og sikre stabil og tidssvarende applikationsdrift i PET\n\nSom applikationsspecialist i PET bliver din overordnede opgave at give kollegaerne i PET de bedst mulige digitale redskaber i det daglige arbejde.\n\nSektionen DevOps udvikler og drifter PET’s centrale systemer og applikationer. Du bliver en del af et team, som har hovedfokus på drift, vedligeholdelse og udvikling af disse systemer.\n\nDet Omfatter Bl.a. At\n\n\n Sikre kontinuerlig drift\n Håndtere fejl, som ikke kan løses af brugersupport\n Release nye versioner\n Opgradere og patche underliggende platforme og OS\n Implementere overvågning, logging, backup og disaster/recovery\n Skalere den underliggende infrastruktur til forretningens behov\n Løse øvrige opgaver relateret til driften af applikationer, systemer og platforme.\n\n\nVi har desuden et stort ønske om en højere grad af automatisering af vores driftsprocesser relateret til applikationerne – både i forhold til nyudviklede og legacy applikationer.\n\nSektionen hører til i PET’s IT-sektor, som er organisatorisk forankret i stabsafdelingen og som leverer, IT-services til hele organisationen. IT-sektoren består af tre centre, et infrastrukturcenter, et Center for Applikationer og et Center for Processer & Support. Disse centre er yderligere opdelt i sektioner, hvor de faglige kompetencer er grupperet med hensyntagen til den bedst mulige understøttelse af leverancerne og faglige fællesskaber.\n\nMange af opgaverne løses i tæt samarbejde med andre kollegaer i IT-sektoren, hvilket betyder, at kommunikation og samarbejde er afgørende for succes. Vores kultur er baseret på samarbejde, tillid og ansvarlighed. Fælles for medarbejderne, er ønsket om at tjene en meningsfyldt sag, som er større end profit og markedsandele.\n\nFå en hverdag, der aldrig bliver hverdag\n\nDet kræver IT-profiler at værne om frihed, mennesker og demokrati og PET er en stor IT-arbejdsplads. Her arbejder java-udviklere, infrastrukturspecialister, netværksteknikere, autodidakte hackere, firewallspecialister og mange andre med en baggrund inden for IT. Nogle har valgt PET for at arbejde med store og komplekse opgaver. Andre faldt for, at vi selv designer mange af vores løsninger fra bunden, udvikler og implementerer dem. Vores kollegaer skal bruge vores arbejde, og vi er med fra start til slut. Endelig har mange af os valgt jobbet for at arbejde med en sag, der er større end profit og timefakturering.\n\nVores arbejdsplads er som ingen andre. Som applikationsspecialist i PET bliver du en del af en hverdag, der er præget af opgaver, som ikke findes andre steder, og hver dag byder på nye udfordringer, som ikke fandtes i går. Vi har en hverdag, der aldrig bliver hverdag, og det kan du også få.\n\nDu har en faglighed inden for applikationer og har mod på at lære nyt, hvor det kræves\n\nVi forventer, at du har dokumenteret erfaring fra lignende roller. Derudover tænker vi, at du har en relevant uddannelse som fx datamatiker, datalog eller softwareingeniør. Vi går op i, at du er sikkerhedsbevidst, har mod på at lære nyt og kommer med en naturlig passion for applikationer.\n\nFor at få succes i rollen er det desuden vigtigt:\n\n\n At du har gode kommunikations- og samarbejdsevner\n At du har erfaring med både traditionel drift og en DevOps-tilgang til drift af applikationer\n At du både har evner og lyst til at arbejde med applikationer, som afvikles i både Windows, Linux og Kubernetes, alternativt er du indstillet på at lære det\n At du har erfaring med automatisering af driftsprocesser og har lyst til at hjælpe dit team hen mod dette mål\n\n\nDerudover er det en fordel, hvis du har erfaring med programmering.\n\nI PET vægter vi desuden visse personlige kompetencer højt. Det er kompetencer, som vi mener, er essentielle for alle PET-ansatte uanset faglig baggrund. Det gør vi, fordi det er vigtigt for os, at vi finder det rette match. Du kan læse om kompetencerne her www.pet.dk/fra-ansoegning-til-ansaettelse.\n\nAnsættelsesforhold\n\nDu kan læse mere om hele PET’s ansættelsesproces på www.pet.dk/job.\n\nAnsættelsesstart pr. 1. oktober 2025. Grundet sommerferie kan der gå et stykke tid, før du hører fra os. Vi håber meget, at du vil være tålmodig med os. Vi forventer at påbegynde samtaler i uge 32.\n\nDit arbejdssted bliver på Klausdalsbrovej 1 i Søborg, lige ved siden af Buddinge station.\n\nHar du en akademisk baggrund, bliver du ansat på overenskomstvilkår i henhold til de til enhver tid gældende aftaler mellem Finansministeriet og Akademikernes Centralorganisation. Har du en anden uddannelsesmæssig baggrund, bliver du ansat på overenskomstvilkår i henhold til den til enhver tid gældende organisationsaftale for kontorfunktionærer i staten mellem Finansministeriet og HK/STAT samt OAO-S-fællesoverenskomst. Alternativt bliver du ansat på anden relevant overenskomst.\n\nEt ansættelsesforhold i PET skal behandles med diskretion, hvilket du som ansøger skal være opmærksom på. Det betyder, at du som udgangspunkt godt kan fortælle tætte og fortrolige relationer, som du har tillid til, at du har søgt en stilling i PET, men ikke hvad jobbet indebærer.\n\nDet er en forudsætning for ansættelse i PET, at du kan sikkerhedsgodkendes til yderst hemmeligt, ligesom du skal kunne opretholde sikkerhedsgodkendelsen gennem hele din ansættelse. Som sikkerhedsgodkendt forventes det, at du er særlig opmærksom på din tavshedspligt i forhold til klassificeret information.\n\nYderligere information \n\nDu er altid meget velkommen til at kontakte os på hverdage på mail hr-rekruttering@politi.dk eller på telefon +45 24 62 18 45, hvis du har spørgsmål til stillingen, PET som arbejdsplads eller lignende.\n\nNår du søger en stilling hos PET, giver du lov til, at vi må indhente dit CPR-nummer via CPR-registeret med henblik på identifikation af dig i forbindelse med rekrutteringsprocessen. Vi indhenter dit CPR-nummer, så vi sikkert kan fremsende relevante og nødvendige dokumenter til dig via Digital Post.\n\nDet er vigtigt for os, at PET afspejler den mangfoldighed, som vi arbejder for. Derfor opfordrer vi alle interesserede, uanset køn, alder, religion, seksualitet og etniske tilhørsforhold til at søge stillingen.\n\nTræd ind i en lukket verden, der åbner nye døre, hvor vi udvikler os, træner og bygger videre på det, vi kan. Om vi udvikler nye systemer, analyserer data eller finjusterer fodstillingen til skydetræning, så er vi altid på tæerne. Det skaber gode muligheder for, at du kan rykke dig med os, vokse med opgaverne og åbne nye døre i dit arbejdsliv.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4240246619/','2025-06-09',NULL,NULL,'[\"Kubernetes\", \"Linux\", \"Styresystemer\", \"CPR-certificeret\", \"Driftsledelse\", \"FX Options\", \"PR\", \"Profiler\", \"Roller\", \"STAT\"]','2025-06-30 11:26:30','2025-06-30 11:26:30'),(27,4249615502,'Back End Developer',27,'Den Europæiske Union','Om jobbet\n\nSenior Backend/Game Engine Developer\n\n\n\n\n• 100% remote\n\n• Salary 75-100K b2b or EOR \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n➡️Main responsabilities\n\nDevelop robust backend systems, RNG models (basic understanding of maths models and game balancing), and game logic engines.\n\n\n\n\n➡️Tech Stack\n\nTypeScript, MySQL, experience with RGS integration. Experience with PHP and/or Go highly beneficial.\n\n\n\n\n➡️Experience\n\nExperience in online gambling games.\n\nMinimum 6+ years in backend development.\n\nGame engine creation, specifically in iGaming products (slots, crash games, table games).','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4249615502/','2025-06-16',100,NULL,'[\"MySQL\", \"PHP\", \"Søg\", \"TypeScript\"]','2025-06-30 11:26:30','2025-06-30 11:26:30'),(28,4239611505,'Applikationsspecialister til en hverdag, der aldrig bliver hverdag i PET',16,'København, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nKunne du tænke dig at levere systemer og applikationer til en organisation, som ikke ligner nogle andre? Er automatisering af driftsprocesser en central del af din værktøjskasse? Og kan du spænde over både legacy og nyudviklede applikationer? Så er du måske vores nye applikationsspecialist i Center for Applikationer.\n\nBliv en del af arbejdet med at modernisere applikationslandskabet og sikre stabil og tidssvarende applikationsdrift i PET\n\nSom applikationsspecialist i PET bliver din overordnede opgave at give kollegaerne i PET de bedst mulige digitale redskaber i det daglige arbejde.\n\nSektionen DevOps udvikler og drifter PET’s centrale systemer og appli